<p>VI<br/>sometimes at Trevellyan.  He remembered being in Camp with Pat at Liverpool -<br/>Looking through some papers today I find a letter from Gen Rosenthal which I intended to enclose in a previous letter to the pater but evidently overlooked it &amp; now enclose it -  [See page 406]<br/>Am awfully glad Mrs Grimley has been taking you for little trips Mum, as it will do you good &ndash; They are certainly very dear people &ndash;<br/>I am writing this with a most beautiful pen which Mary sent me &ndash;<br/>There appears to be a dearth of news tonight</p>
